76561198079853514,Recommended,266290,30481854,Posted: 12 March,all,adenis123,"I have been a virtual pilot for many years on MSFS (FS2002, FS2004, FSX) and fly on occasions, add-on helicopters such as the awesome Dodosim Bell 206 for FSX.Must point out that it causes me many CDT's, even when scenery and weather settings are to minimal.But that's another subject entirely.My expectations were real low of this ""game"", after reading the absolute bashing of reviews.Of course the helicopters in Search and Rescue are not comparable to highly simulated models such as the Flight One Bell 206, and Aerosoft Sikorsky BlackHawk, neither the UH-1A, KA-50, and Mi-8MTV2 from DCS products.The term ""Simulator"" should be removed from the description, to diminish the negativity it receives by the boat full.Concerning controls configurations, I had not much success pairing my Thrustmaster Hotas T-Flite X and ""brother"" T-Flite Stick X.When operating cyclic inputs, the view changed automatically, creating random points of views.Going back and forth in the menu, was not fruitful.I could not deactivate the unintended view actions from thoses axes.I will retry later.My new Logitech F310 gamepad came to the ""rescue"", and I was quite surprised by it's compatibility with this title.I do believe that it is a Cardinal sin to fly a helicopter without a proper joystick (and pedals if possible), but again this reviewer was very impressed with the results of the F310.I tried mapping the controls of the gamepad, but this was not going to happen.I accepted the default mapping of the Logitech Gamepad buttons, and within 20 minutes the adaptation was very intuitive.Many scenery details were realized when I got to use HSSR, mainly the eye candy features all around me when walking around the airport.Vapors emanating from the hot tarmac, tropical birds flying and singing, falling leaves from moving trees, animated trucks, cars, and people in the vincinity, detailed clouds with movements, sun rays creating shadows, a full moon, superb water effects, well modeled structures and buildings ect.Talking about water effects, in one those missions with heavy rain, I would suggest strongly to the developers, installing windshield wipers.They do exists on simulated helicopters.In fact for the veterans of a SAR 4, some might remember having them, even though they were not utilized to their real efficiency back then.Must point out that ATC communications are accurate but passive, meaning no interactions are provided.Radio shatter is on a rather short loop mode, but at least phonetic alphabet is used and quite immersing.The omissions of very annoying timers counting down for the success of missions, are fortunately no where to be seen.I must specify that I have not completed the game, and hope they don't materialize.Unless a ""bingo"" fuel situation is implemented in the future, that would be an exception.I would priorize the possibility of having a  ""save progress"" option during a mission.The menu should let the player select these options if desired:Unlock all missions, and all helicopters.Bonuses are to be earned though.The free flight mode should offer the pilot the choice of weather, all regions, all Helicopters.My computer is quite old and still on Windows XP, because of it's compatibility with MSFS, and the multitude of marvelous add-ons for each year. I have been lucky so far with reliability.FPS were a serious issue on start up, until major alterations were done to the scenery/video options.The absence of choosing ""simple clouds"" in the menu, must be offered without a doubt.It sure does not contribute to some flexibility towards better frame rates.This important option is offered on MSFS and Take On Helicopters for example.Missions with heavy rain, combined with beautiful stormy clouds and ocean swells, are a real frame rate killer.Again, my set up (OS) has many ""wrinkles"", and needs all the help it can get.In conclusion, for people not plagued with technical problems, and open minded to plain fun, challenges, and precision flying inputs, will conclude that this game is not bad after all.Very far from it, in my modest opinion.Come to think of it, this purchase was cheaper than the majority of my scenery addons on DVD's for MSFS.I might add that Aerosoft's Nice Airport for FS9 and FSX (DVD), is absolutely stunning.That software is more expensive of course, and readers know very well, that it is in a completely different category.The developers of HSRS must be fully credited for their availability to improve and listen, in regards to customers issues and requests.The proof of these efforts are in the discussions section of Steam, and in updates (actual version 1.068) since it's release in 2014.More impressions will follow in the very near future.So long fellow virtual pilots.A.Latest update from hell: Completely stuck on mission 6.Read all the tips on this site and watched videos on you tube to no avail.Second update: I seriously think that this mission is bugged, meaning that by pure coincidence it worked.After a long rest of the game I gave it another shot, doing the exact things as before and somehow it worked. I still wonder at what worked?Here are a few tips that don't garantee you anything at all...1- Forget the red circle on the map, it is misleading.2- Use auto-hover directly over the flames.3- Fly between 50-80 feet in the thick of it.4- Girate and do slow back and forth motions, all the while using the E button 2 or 3 times.Be careful not to disengage Auto-Hover, by being too rough on the controls.On this miraculous event, only 2 buckets of water were needed. Go figure.I will say again that all these steps were tried before, and without results.Curiously on fhis last attempt right after climbing on board the chopper, the game advised of an error.Closed everything and got back on Steam, went on the mission, and by pure coincidence I made it. Was this a factor that played a role in the previous fails?I had done a cache integrity of the game in the past.At the end of this mission you have to release your empty container of water at your base, and if your forgot that the ""G"" key lets it go, you will not be able to finish this ""lovely"" mission...I had tried this mission way too many times, and something is terribly wrong here.Trust me on that one.A cheat code ""Skip Mission"" is needed badly, when a software glitch is obviously the culprit here.Was this a random event, that the software ""decided"" to make me finally stop the forest fire?I will never replay that mission. Ever.Epilogue: European theater mission #4. Again stuck with mission fires to stop, carbon copy of mission #6 first version.Have tried 20 times, that is it.I quit for good.My lemon award to the people who designed those bugged missions.You should not been part of this game, you ruined it.PS: A SAVE OPTION DURING MISSIONS MUST BE IMPLEMENTED ASAP."
