76561198064388679,Recommended,266290,25473447,"Posted: 11 September, 2016",all,ZenZone1,"Update 2 - Sep 30, 2016More on physics- There's strong wind effect during stormy weather which makes landing hazardous. Heavier chopper mitigates it but reduces room to manoeuver.Difficulty- Hard when landing spots are located in tight spaces although plenty of space is available nearby. Easy when trees aren't solid.Update 2 - Sep 19, 2016 - editing and some additional infoTL;DRIMO this game is awesome! BUT mission design shows lack of careful planning. Maps have interesting landmarks worthy of some sighseeing trips.Update 1 - Sep 14, 2016Mouse control:Mouse works in 2 modes but it doesn't turn like an FPS shooter; left/right banks and up/down pitches the copter. Turning left or right requires pressing left or right button and the response is identical to pressing the keys A or D; they both seem to rely on repeat rate.GraphicsPerformance drops in the vicinity of buildings and/or when weather effects are on. This is normal, no cause for disappointment here. Turning off some options or lowering them improves frame rate; 60 fps is achievable except during heavy rain but that may be due to my rig running on potato chips.Search light has no blend or dispersion, it has hard edge.Glitches1) When returning the water bucket to it's original location, if it wasn't dropped from the correct height it stays put in mid-air.2) Western Europe map, mission 4. Stuck truck doesn't appear 2b lifted but mission can still be completed.3) Exiting chopper too soon b4 mission is declared successful prevents completion of mission.https://youtu.be/VrxMEOyAfbEGameplayThere is no campaign or career mode hence no economic aspect of simulation like costs of purchase, repair, fuel or salaries. No worries about resources needed for operations. Incidentally fuel is either unlimited or a non-issue and no mission is time limited which means great stress free flying experience. You only need to master flying the different types of choppers and skillful handling of tasks. By now you might realize that proficiency at different tasks is directly proportional to flying skills and requires fine control. Auto hover is very helpful in this regard but there are achievements which can only be attained by non-reliance on auto hover.The same mission may take place at different time and weather conditions. Time and weather conditions change from mission to mission presumably calculated based on time taken per mission and free-flight mode. There is a manual override feature where you can set your preferred conditions however certain missions may have preset conditions.PhysicsDifferences in helicopters' handling and engine sound are noticeable. Heavier choppers handle predictably like a fat cow if cows can fly that is. Physics has 2 modes; accelerated collective means double tap of ascend or descend keys causes max rate of climb or descend respectively. Non-accelerated means more gradual and natural elevation changes.Flight controlis understandably difficult for many people because auto-centering / levelling is too slow except when auto-hover is used but auto-hover degrades flying into a stop and go motion unless the keyboard is repeatedly and rapidly pressed. Perhaps using a mouse or other controller could smoothen movement.Music and soundOMG music is grating and annoying; frequent use of brass crescendos give the impression of flying in a warzone. There are several tracks but all sound samey. Fortunately music level can be turned down to zero.The seemingly random radio chatter though is quite interesting. It seems to be aware of what you're doing or seeing and respond accordingly or it may just be coincidental i'm not sure which. Perhaps it's just a collection of com chatter / phrases played at random. Additional feature like some direct communications with Control Tower would be awesome but i don't think it's essential since this game is about tasks rather procedures.  The inclusion of com chatter add  to the atmosphere of piloting.All in all, i'm still pleased with this game as it provides a wide selection of helicopters to fly and a variety of tasks requiring various degrees of precision and technique to perform. Still recommended, especially for SimCopter fans.First basic review belowBought this in a PlayWay Sim Bundle when it was on sale. Great deal, every other game in the bundle works but this, won't even run. It CTD as soon as it's launched. So i shelved it and hoped to play it later after i could upgrade to a new desktop PC. The game's system requirement give no assurance that it would work on laptop GPU. Needless to say i was a little disappointed but i already got my money's worth due to the bundle discount.That was some time ago. Today i had the inexplicable feeling of being lucky so i installed it again and voila! it worked! Frankly i'm not sure what gives, i tried every trick or tweak i know prior to this and it didn't work. My best guess is that it may have something to do with either the fact that it's installed to C drive or that i had to manually assign High Performance mode to AMD Catalyst app or both but i'm sure i did that before and it didn't work.Anyway the game runs smooth at 1280x720 in high detail with AA at medium, Anisotropic Filtering On, Bloom On, view range set to high, shadows quality medium, Depth Blur On and Motion Blur On. Those are the settings set as default on first run. It's playable and there's no noticeable lag considering that the game recorder was also running and recording the game as it is played. One thing that might be different this time was that it was running at 720p windowed mode on my external monitor. I remember now that not all games can run at 720p on my laptop native resolution of 1366 x 768.Options available in menus:http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BdkkaGmuxMsSo take note of 3 important points if you're using a laptop with AMD Radeon GPU:Install on C driveSet AMD Catalyst driver app to use High Performance mode. This may need to be done manually if the game crashes immediately.Try diverting display output to external monitor which supports 720p.Now that we've got some technicalities out of the way, lets move on to a basic review as i've not played much of this game as of yet.Graphics quality - i haven't scrutinized the trees or the NPCs closely as these serve decorative rather than functional elements but looking at the scenery from any of the helicopter views, the scenery looks good. The Depth of Field blur effect and AA works really well. There is no noticeable sawtooth lines in slanted menu boxes, helicopter models or cockpit frames. The distant blur effect is well blended and the draw distance is sufficiently far enough to prevent objects from popping-up at the last seconds.Can't comment on the authenticity of rotor sounds due to my lack of familiarity with helicopters. However the sounds seem to be positionally correct. Cockpit sounds are muffled compared to external sounds so that adds to the sense of immersion.Flight control with keyboard is well done. With mouse you probably need to lower sensitivity level a notch or two.Mission requirements are a bit exacting, it appears that positioning the helicopter for drop-off or pick-up have very small activation areas.Mission 1:http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zOvUr4M8cUcI haven't seen any bugs, glitches or crashes yet but maybe it's too early to tell, will update if there are any changes. From what i've seen and experienced so far, i like this game. And the fact that SAR games are rather rare, i'm glad i have this on my repertoire of games to play.One last note: There is weather effects based on what i've seen on YT.Score as of today: 6/10"
