,Recommended,266290,9364088,"Posted: 6 March, 2014",all,Porter,"After a couple updates the game is now working for me on windows 7 64 bit. Thanks guys for the update which fixed what ever the initial problems were :)As for gameplay it's actually fun. Graphics were decent. As for controls I played with keyboard and mouse and that worked nicely. You can either use keyboard only or mouse only or even both at the same time which I thought was nice. Sadly I wasnt able to configure and assign the proper buttons and axis on my hotas joystick and throttle, and the throttle didnt work at all. Aside from that it wasnt too bad. The game just flat out refused to recognize my combat rudder pedels and it seemed to intergrate it all into the joystick. Also tried an xbox controller and it was ok for the most part except on the right thumbstick where it seemed a bit too sensitive or something cause it would pan the camera views by itself when I tried to pan around, even a little touch would set it off wandering around the screen. And yes I did calbrate it in windows before I played. This usually dosnt happen in other games when using the xbox 360 controller. I might suggest to add settings to adjust sensitivity.All in all I'd definately recommend this game as it has a lot of potential. The tutorial and missons were fun, the controls were easy to learn and intuitive using mouse and keyboard. It's not too easy but not too hard either like alot of other flight sims I've played, you know like the kind that might turn off newer players to the genre. So it strikes a good balance between realism and ease of use with a not so steep learning curve.Definately looking forward to playing all the missions and flying all the helicopters now. And this is coming from a hardcore flight sim fan who has played them all."
