,Not Recommended,266290,14166660,"Posted: 25 January, 2015",all,DaveBraveShave,"It's not very good, not even as a joke.I bought it because I had a dollar looking at me on my Steam account and I decided I wanted to get a funny and broken game. The problem is that it isn't really that type of game. It's not as broken and silly as other simulators, but It's also not a very good representation of flying an actual helicopter and saving people. The game is exceedingly average I think. The flying controls are rather basic and a few automations that the game gives you (auto hover comes to mind) destroy whatever fun the game can offer. Once you realize this the game is just a repetitive mess. It has maybe two songs in it, some rudimentary character models and animations. The environment is pretty bland, generic, and muddy looking, and to top it all off the game has an unnecessarily annoying depth of field that is too blurry and shifts focus too often.The game is quirky in these regards as the animations, voice acting, and character models are laughably pathetic, but that can only really carry the experience a half an hour at most. The rest of my playtime was spent looking for a way to find utility in such a bland game.  Needless to say, I never found it."
